<h2 class="subtitle">Pointers in Entertainment</h2>
</div>

<div>
<p class="bodytext">
  In the world of gaming, pointers have also been necessary for the user to navigate the very varied interfaces of videogames. Most of the times, pointers are designed around the theme and style
  of the game itself. Pointers in videogames come in all shapes and sizes. Any console and game that requires them, has their own unique pointer.
</p>

<p class="bodytext down">
  Consoles with handheld pointing devices such as Nintendo's Wii and the Playstation Move, introduced a new need for on-screen
   cursors. The player physically points to the screen with the remote and the pointer follows this motion as accurately as it can.
   While the appearance of these pointers does change and the designs are varied, in-game, the actual purpose of the pointer is
    simpler than in a computer. They are used almost always to navigate menus, to choose a fighter, or to aim some sort of weapon.


<p class="bodytext lower">
    In most videogames though, pointers are not necessary at all. Instead, the keyboard on a computer or buttons on a controller
    or handheld device are favored.

</p>

<p class="dangerous">
  It's dangerous to go alone! Click on one of these.
</p>
